# Protection Control which CRUD operations require authentication per entity. ## Quick Options The option accepts shortcuts for common patterns: | Value | list | get | create | update | remove | |-------|------|-----|--------|--------|--------| | (default) | public | public | public | public | public | | | public | public | protected | protected | protected | | or | protected | protected | protected | protected | protected | ## Granular Control For fine-grained control, pass an object: ## Generated Router The protection settings translate to procedure types in tRPC: ## Examples by Use Case ### Blog Posts (public read, auth write) ### User Profiles (fully protected) ### Products (public catalog, admin write) ### Comments (custom pattern) ## Accessing User in Mutations Protected procedures have access to the authenticated user via context: ## Requirements Protection requires authentication to be enabled in your config: Without auth enabled, all entities are public regardless of the setting. protected typescript
export const Post = defineEntity('Post', {
  fields: { ... },
  protected: 'write',  // Most common: reads public, writes protected
})


| Value | list | get | create | update | remove |
|-------|------|-----|--------|--------|--------|
|   (default) | public | public | public | public | public |
|   | public | public | protected | protected | protected |
|   or   | protected | protected | protected | protected | protected |

## Granular Control

For fine-grained control, pass an object:

 typescript
export const Comment = defineEntity('Comment', {
  fields: {
    content: text().required(),
  },
  protected: {
    list: false,      // Anyone can list comments
    get: false,       // Anyone can view a comment
    create: true,     // Must be logged in to create
    update: true,     // Must be logged in to update
    remove: true,     // Must be logged in to remove
  },
})


## Generated Router

The protection settings translate to procedure types in tRPC:

 typescript
// generated/trpc/routers/comment.ts
import { publicProcedure, protectedProcedure } from '../trpc'

export const commentRouter = router({
  list: publicProcedure.query(async ({ ctx }) => {
    // No auth check
    return db.select().from(comments)
  }),

  get: publicProcedure
    .input(z.string())
    .query(async ({ input }) => {
      // No auth check
      return db.select().from(comments).where(eq(comments.id, input))
    }),

  create: protectedProcedure
    .input(commentCreateSchema)
    .mutation(async ({ input, ctx }) => {
      // ctx.session is guaranteed to exist
      return db.insert(comments).values(input)
    }),

  update: protectedProcedure
    .input(commentUpdateSchema)
    .mutation(async ({ input, ctx }) => {
      return db.update(comments).set(input.data).where(eq(comments.id, input.id))
    }),

  remove: protectedProcedure
    .input(z.string())
    .mutation(async ({ input, ctx }) => {
      return db.delete(comments).where(eq(comments.id, input))
    }),
})


## Examples by Use Case

### Blog Posts (public read, auth write)

 typescript
export const Post = defineEntity('Post', {
  fields: {
    title: text().required(),
    content: text().required(),
    published: boolean().default(false),
  },
  protected: 'write',
})


### User Profiles (fully protected)

 typescript
export const UserProfile = defineEntity('UserProfile', {
  fields: {
    bio: text().optional(),
    website: text().optional().url(),
  },
  protected: 'all',
})


### Products (public catalog, admin write)

 typescript
export const Product = defineEntity('Product', {
  fields: {
    name: text().required(),
    price: number().required().positive(),
  },
  protected: 'write',
  // Note: For role-based access, implement in hooks
})


### Comments (custom pattern)

 typescript
export const Comment = defineEntity('Comment', {
  fields: {
    content: text().required(),
  },
  protected: {
    list: false,    // Public timeline
    get: false,     // Public permalinks
    create: true,   // Login to comment
    update: true,   // Login to edit
    remove: true,   // Login to delete
  },
})


## Accessing User in Mutations

Protected procedures have access to the authenticated user via context:

 typescript
// In hooks or custom logic
export const postHooks = {
  async beforeCreate(input, ctx) {
    // ctx.user is guaranteed for protected procedures
    return {
      ...input,
      authorId: ctx.user.id,
    }
  },
}


## Requirements

Protection requires authentication to be enabled in your config:

 typescript
export default defineConfig({
  entities: [...],
  auth: {
    enabled: true,
    providers: ['credentials'],
  },
})


Without auth enabled, all entities are public regardless of the  typescript export const Post defineEntity Post fields protected write Most common reads public writes protected typescript export const Comment defineEntity Comment fields content text required protected list false Anyone list comments false Anyone view comment create true Must logged create update true Must logged update remove true Must logged remove typescript generated trpc routers comment import publicProcedure protectedProcedure from trpc export const commentRouter router list publicProcedure query async auth check return select from comments publicProcedure input string query async input auth check return select from comments where comments input create protectedProcedure input commentCreateSchema mutation async input session guaranteed exist return insert comments values input update protectedProcedure input commentUpdateSchema mutation async input return update comments input data where comments input remove protectedProcedure input string mutation async input return delete comments where comments input typescript export const Post defineEntity Post fields title text required content text required published boolean default false protected write typescript export const UserProfile defineEntity UserProfile fields text optional website text optional protected typescript export const Product defineEntity Product fields name text required price number required positive protected write Note role based access implement hooks typescript export const Comment defineEntity Comment fields content text required protected list false Public timeline false Public permalinks create true Login comment update true Login edit remove true Login delete typescript hooks custom logic export const postHooks async beforeCreate input user guaranteed protected procedures return input authorId user typescript export default defineConfig entities auth enabled true providers credentials

