# Hooks Hooks let you run custom business logic before and after CRUD operations without modifying generated code. ## Enabling Hooks Enable hooks per entity: Or enable specific hooks: ## Generated Files After running : ## Hook Types ## Implementing Hooks Edit the generated hook file: ## Common Patterns ### Auto-assign Author ### Validate Stock ### Send Notifications ### Audit Logging ### Prevent Deletion ## Error Handling Throw errors in hooks to abort the operation: Errors in hooks are logged but don't rollback the operation. typescript
export const Order = defineEntity('Order', {
  fields: {
    total: number().required(),
    status: text().default('pending'),
  },
  hooks: true,  // Enable all hooks
})


Or enable specific hooks:

 typescript
hooks: {
  beforeCreate: true,
  afterCreate: true,
  beforeUpdate: true,
  afterUpdate: true,
  beforeRemove: true,
  afterRemove: true,
}


## Generated Files

