# Behaviors Behaviors are built-in patterns that add common functionality to entities. Enable them in the option. ## Available Behaviors ### timestamps Adds and fields that are automatically managed. Generated fields: The field is automatically updated on every modification. ### softDelete Adds a field instead of permanently deleting records. Generated field: Generated router behavior: - and automatically filter out soft-deleted records - sets instead of - To permanently delete, use the database directly ## Combining Behaviors Enable multiple behaviors: ## Example Usage ### With Timestamps ### With Soft Delete ## Future Behaviors Planned behaviors for future releases: | Behavior | Description | |----------|-------------| | | Log all changes to an audit table | | | Keep history of all record versions | | | Auto-generate URL slugs from a field | behaviors createdAt updatedAt typescript
export const Post = defineEntity('Post', {
  fields: {
    title: text().required(),
  },
  behaviors: {
    timestamps: true,
  },
})


**Generated fields:**
 typescript
createdAt: integer('created_at').notNull().$defaultFn(() => Date.now()),
updatedAt: integer('updated_at').notNull().$defaultFn(() => Date.now()),


The   field is automatically updated on every modification.

### softDelete

Adds a   field instead of permanently deleting records.

 typescript
export const User = defineEntity('User', {
  fields: {
    email: text().required().email(),
  },
  behaviors: {
    softDelete: true,
  },
})


**Generated field:**
 typescript
deletedAt: integer('deleted_at'),  // null = not deleted


**Generated router behavior:**
-   and   automatically filter out soft-deleted records
-   sets   instead of  
- To permanently delete, use the database directly

## Combining Behaviors

Enable multiple behaviors:

 typescript
export const Document = defineEntity('Document', {
  fields: {
    title: text().required(),
    content: text().optional(),
  },
  behaviors: {
    timestamps: true,   // createdAt, updatedAt
    softDelete: true,   // deletedAt
  },
})


## Example Usage

### With Timestamps

 typescript
// Created record includes timestamps
const post = await trpc.post.create.mutate({
  title: 'Hello World',
})
// { id: '...', title: 'Hello World', createdAt: 1703001234567, updatedAt: 1703001234567 }

// Updated record has new updatedAt
const updated = await trpc.post.update.mutate({
  id: post.id,
  title: 'Updated Title',
})
// { ..., updatedAt: 1703001234999 }


### With Soft Delete

 typescript
// Remove sets deletedAt instead of deleting
await trpc.user.remove.mutate(userId)

// List excludes soft-deleted records
const users = await trpc.user.list.query()
// Only returns users where deletedAt is null

// Soft-deleted records still exist in database
// Access directly for admin/restore functionality


